                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3xs5k32j/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>makes her discontinue it.</p>\n            <p><persName>Abm Stein</persName> also not only will not take<lb/> it but will not\n                pay—he says when<lb/> he last paid you he told you not<lb/> to send it again, for he\n                never reads it.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">After calling a number of times<lb/> on\n                    <persName>Ritterband</persName> he <sic>shewd</sic> me at last<lb/> your\n                Receipts for 12.00 paid in <date>May 55</date><lb/> up to <date>March 1855</date>\n                &amp; yet I hold Bills<lb/> against him for 12.00 while he only owes<lb/> 3.00 part\n                of the last Bill for 2 years<lb/> I am often made to look very foolish<lb/> when so\n                many dispute their accounts<lb/> &amp; in cases they are right. I look<lb/>\n                anxiously for the time when you<lb/> may be here yourself to see to the<lb/> matter,\n                as so many have refused to<lb/> continue taking your paper.<lb/> I really do not\n                know what to<lb/> make of it—what has come over<lb/> the people. Do send the parcel\n                in<lb/> time next week that the man<lb/> have time to give them out.<lb/> The last\n                was not delivered till<lb/>\n                <date>Saturday, the 7<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> last &amp; therefore<lb/> the man\n                did not deliver them</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3xs5k32j/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
